        <updateDate>2013-03-23T15:01:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Historic Homeownership Revitalization Act of 2013 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) allow a new tax credit for 20% of rehabilitation expenditures for a historic home used as a principal residence, up to $60,000; and (2) increase the rehabilitation tax credit for residential rental property located in economically distressed areas with high construction costs. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
